item.title: About
item.dc:creator: admin_test
item.content:encoded:
Members: John Clint, Steve Humbert, Shawn Galahan, Chris Complita

About: The Band

Sounds Like:

Arctic Monkeys, Foo Fighters and Generation X

Bio:

Recovery Ball is hard rock! We deliver a high energy set of in your face metal with a melodic tone that we like to call art! We're a 4 piece with 2 guitars, bass and drums. We'll basically play anywhere, anytime and anyplace! Check us out before we meet our inevitable rock n roll demise!

item.title: Plug-ins for bands
item.dc:creator: admin_test
item.content:encoded:
Here is a list of the plug-in features I hope to add as a major part of my content.
  • Gig Press
  • Sound Cloud
  • Face book
I choose these features by looking at what commercial available WordPress themes for bands offered up in there sites.Here is what Sound Cloud and Gig Press could look like in the side bar. [caption id="attachment_121" align="alignleft" width="160"] Just and Example of :
Sound Cloud and
Gig Press[/caption]

item.title: Researching Band Web sites
item.dc:creator: admin_test
item.content:encoded: In my research of Band web site, I was looking at both style and functionality. I Google top Band themes and came upon this: 25 of the Best Websites of Bands and Musicians It gave me more than a few ideas. I also found this theme building design team and I like their work the best :Foxhound.com Both set of resource have given me ideas about what features to emulate, site structure differences for music based web sites and ideas about plug-ins I would like to look at . If I did not need to build this site from scratch I would purchase one of the very affordable themes from Foxhound Band themes.
